parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The EPS warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or feels loose
the vehicle is hard to steer
the power steering assist fails
the steering wheel jerks or pulls to one side
the vehicle is unable to make turns
the steering column has excessive play.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard stays illuminated
the passenger airbag light fails to illuminate
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
or the airbag fails to deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of airbags can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without any apparent reason
such as a collision or impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbag sensors can prevent the airbags from deploying in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard stays illuminated
the passenger airbag light fails to illuminate
or the airbag fails to deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake lights on the instrument panel
ABS lights on the instrument panel
smoking or burning smell from the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
passenger seat weight classification sensor failure
airbag system shutdown
no airbag deployment in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, loss of vehicle control, or other safety hazards.
symptoms: Smoking or burning smell from the vehicle
electrical shorts
blown fuses
malfunctioning lights
alarm system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose traction or stability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: ABS lights on the instrument panel
smoking or burning smell from the brakes
brake pedal pulsation or vibration.
